<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <h4>Introduction</h4>
    <p>
        Welcome to you our Claims Management System. Your privacy is important to us.
        This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal data.
    </p>

    <h4>Information We Collect</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>User credentials</li>
        <li>Your name, email, and assigned role</li>
        <li>Claim information</li>
        <li>Timestamps</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>How We Use Your Information</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>To authenticate and authorize users</li>
        <li>To submit, track, and process claims</li>
        <li>To generate administrative reports</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Data Sharing</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Required by law or institutional policy</li>
        <li>Shared internally for claim processing purposes</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Data Security</h4>
    <p>
        We implement encryption and secure storage to protect all submitted documents and personal data.
    </p>

    <h4>Your Rights</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>View the data we store about you</li>
        <li>Request corrections or deletions</li>
        <li>Withdraw pending claims</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Changes to This Policy</h4>
    <p>
        We may update this policy occasionally.
    </p>

    <h4>Contact Us</h4>
    <p>
        For questions or concerns about this policy, please contact your system administrator or IT support:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:support@system.local">support@system.local</a></li>
        <li>Phone: (011) 589 7894</li>
    </ul>
</div>
